# Build-time config for the Electron desktop app. Copy to `.env`.
#
# Discord application (client) ID for Rich Presence ("Listening to Lumen").
# Create an application at https://discord.com/developers/applications and
# paste its ID here. Leave blank to keep Rich Presence off.
#
# The `electron:compile` step bakes this into the packaged app (a
# DISCORD_CLIENT_ID environment variable wins over this file). At runtime,
# `discordClientId` in the app's config.json overrides the baked-in value.
DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=
